{
  "id": "precalculus-ch07-sec05",
  "title": "Chapter Review",
  "chapter": 7,
  "section": 5,
  "book": "precalculus",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "connection",
      "id": "connection-7.5",
      "number": null,
      "title": "Connecting the Threads",
      "content": "This chapter has woven together many strands: fundamental identities, \nsum and difference formulas, double and half angles, and techniques for \nsolving equations. Like the interconnected stories of Scripture, each \npiece supports the others. The Pythagorean identity leads to the \ndouble-angle formulas; the sum formulas unlock the half-angle results; \nevery identity becomes a tool for solving equations. As you review, \nlook for these connections—they're the real treasure of mathematics."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This chapter developed the major trigonometric identities and their \napplications. Here we gather the key results and practice applying \nthem in varied contexts."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Summary of Key Identities"
    },
    {
      "type": "summary",
      "id": "summary-7.5",
      "number": null,
      "title": "Fundamental Identities",
      "content": "**Reciprocal:**\n\\[\n\\csc\\theta = \\frac{1}{\\sin\\theta}, \\quad \n\\sec\\theta = \\frac{1}{\\cos\\theta}, \\quad \n\\cot\\theta = \\frac{1}{\\tan\\theta}\n\\]\n\n**Quotient:**\n\\[\n\\tan\\theta = \\frac{\\sin\\theta}{\\cos\\theta}, \\quad \n\\cot\\theta = \\frac{\\cos\\theta}{\\sin\\theta}\n\\]\n\n**Pythagorean:**\n$$\n\\sin^2\\theta + \\cos^2\\theta &= 1 \\\\\n1 + \\tan^2\\theta &= \\sec^2\\theta \\\\\n1 + \\cot^2\\theta &= \\csc^2\\theta\n$$\n\n**Even-Odd:**\n\\[\n\\sin(-\\theta) = -\\sin\\theta, \\quad \n\\cos(-\\theta) = \\cos\\theta, \\quad \n\\tan(-\\theta) = -\\tan\\theta\n\\]"
    },
    {
      "type": "summary",
      "id": "summary-7.5",
      "number": null,
      "title": "Sum and Difference Formulas",
      "content": "$$\n\\sin(\\alpha + \\beta) &= \\sin\\alpha\\cos\\beta + \\cos\\alpha\\sin\\beta \\\\\n\\sin(\\alpha - \\beta) &= \\sin\\alpha\\cos\\beta - \\cos\\alpha\\sin\\beta \\\\[6pt]\n\\cos(\\alpha + \\beta) &= \\cos\\alpha\\cos\\beta - \\sin\\alpha\\sin\\beta \\\\\n\\cos(\\alpha - \\beta) &= \\cos\\alpha\\cos\\beta + \\sin\\alpha\\sin\\beta \\\\[6pt]\n\\tan(\\alpha + \\beta) &= \\frac{\\tan\\alpha + \\tan\\beta}{1 - \\tan\\alpha\\tan\\beta} \\\\[6pt]\n\\tan(\\alpha - \\beta) &= \\frac{\\tan\\alpha - \\tan\\beta}{1 + \\tan\\alpha\\tan\\beta}\n$$"
    },
    {
      "type": "summary",
      "id": "summary-7.5",
      "number": null,
      "title": "Double-Angle and Half-Angle Formulas",
      "content": "**Double-Angle:**\n$$\n\\sin 2\\theta &= 2\\sin\\theta\\cos\\theta \\\\\n\\cos 2\\theta &= \\cos^2\\theta - \\sin^2\\theta = 2\\cos^2\\theta - 1 = 1 - 2\\sin^2\\theta \\\\\n\\tan 2\\theta &= \\frac{2\\tan\\theta}{1 - \\tan^2\\theta}\n$$\n\n**Power-Reducing:**\n\\[\n\\sin^2\\theta = \\frac{1 - \\cos 2\\theta}{2}, \\quad \n\\cos^2\\theta = \\frac{1 + \\cos 2\\theta}{2}\n\\]\n\n**Half-Angle:**\n$$\n\\sin\\frac{\\theta}{2} &= \\pm\\sqrt{\\frac{1 - \\cos\\theta}{2}} \\\\\n\\cos\\frac{\\theta}{2} &= \\pm\\sqrt{\\frac{1 + \\cos\\theta}{2}} \\\\\n\\tan\\frac{\\theta}{2} &= \\frac{1 - \\cos\\theta}{\\sin\\theta} = \\frac{\\sin\\theta}{1 + \\cos\\theta}\n$$"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Problem-Solving Strategies"
    },
    {
      "type": "summary",
      "id": "summary-7.5",
      "number": null,
      "title": "Verifying Identities",
      "content": "1. Work with one side only (usually the more complex side)\n\n2. Convert to sines and cosines\n\n3. Look for Pythagorean identity opportunities\n\n4. Factor expressions when possible\n\n5. Multiply by conjugates for expressions like $1 \\pm \\sin\\theta$\n\n6. Combine fractions over common denominators"
    },
    {
      "type": "summary",
      "id": "summary-7.5",
      "number": null,
      "title": "Solving Trigonometric Equations",
      "content": "1. Isolate the trigonometric function\n\n2. Find the reference angle\n\n3. Identify all solutions using ASTC and the unit circle\n\n4. For multiple angles ($n\\theta$), extend the interval by factor $n$\n\n5. Check for extraneous solutions when squaring\n\n6. Use identities to convert to a single function when needed"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Review Exercises"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Verifying Identities**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Verify each identity."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$\\csc\\theta - \\sin\\theta = \\cot\\theta\\cos\\theta$",
        "$\\dfrac{1 + \\tan^2\\theta}{\\tan^2\\theta} = \\csc^2\\theta$",
        "$\\dfrac{\\sec\\theta - 1}{\\tan\\theta} = \\dfrac{\\tan\\theta}{\\sec\\theta + 1}$",
        "$\\dfrac{\\sin\\theta}{1 + \\cos\\theta} + \\dfrac{1 + \\cos\\theta}{\\sin\\theta} = 2\\csc\\theta$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Verify each identity."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$\\dfrac{1 - \\sin\\theta}{\\cos\\theta} = \\dfrac{\\cos\\theta}{1 + \\sin\\theta}$",
        "$\\sec^2\\theta\\csc^2\\theta = \\sec^2\\theta + \\csc^2\\theta$",
        "$(\\sin\\theta + \\cos\\theta)^2 + (\\sin\\theta - \\cos\\theta)^2 = 2$",
        "$\\tan\\theta + \\cot\\theta = \\sec\\theta\\csc\\theta$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Sum, Difference, and Multiple Angle Formulas**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Find the exact value."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$\\sin 15°$",
        "$\\cos 75°$",
        "$\\tan 105°$",
        "$\\sin\\dfrac{5\\pi}{12}$",
        "$\\cos\\dfrac{7\\pi}{12}$",
        "$\\tan\\dfrac{\\pi}{12}$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Simplify to a single trigonometric function."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$\\sin 5x\\cos 2x - \\cos 5x\\sin 2x$",
        "$\\cos 3\\theta\\cos\\theta + \\sin 3\\theta\\sin\\theta$",
        "$2\\sin 4t\\cos 4t$",
        "$\\cos^2 3x - \\sin^2 3x$",
        "$1 - 2\\sin^2\\dfrac{\\theta}{2}$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If $\\sin\\alpha = \\dfrac{4}{5}$ (QI) and $\\cos\\beta = -\\dfrac{5}{13}$ (QII), find:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$\\sin(\\alpha + \\beta)$",
        "$\\cos(\\alpha - \\beta)$",
        "$\\tan(\\alpha + \\beta)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If $\\sin\\theta = -\\dfrac{5}{13}$ with $\\theta$ in QIII, find:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$\\sin 2\\theta$",
        "$\\cos 2\\theta$",
        "$\\tan 2\\theta$",
        "$\\sin\\dfrac{\\theta}{2}$",
        "$\\cos\\dfrac{\\theta}{2}$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Find the exact value using half-angle formulas."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$\\sin 22.5°$",
        "$\\cos 112.5°$",
        "$\\tan\\dfrac{\\pi}{8}$",
        "$\\sin\\dfrac{3\\pi}{8}$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Solving Equations**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve for $0 \\le \\theta < 2\\pi$."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$2\\sin\\theta - \\sqrt{3} = 0$",
        "$2\\cos\\theta + 1 = 0$",
        "$\\tan\\theta = \\sqrt{3}$",
        "$\\sec\\theta = -2$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve for $0 \\le x < 2\\pi$."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$2\\sin^2 x - 1 = 0$",
        "$\\cos^2 x = \\cos x$",
        "$2\\cos^2 x - 5\\cos x + 2 = 0$",
        "$\\tan^2 x - 3 = 0$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve for $0 \\le \\theta < 2\\pi$."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$\\sin 2\\theta = -\\dfrac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}$",
        "$\\cos 2x = \\dfrac{1}{2}$",
        "$\\tan 3\\theta = 0$",
        "$2\\cos 2\\theta + 1 = 0$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve for $0 \\le \\theta < 2\\pi$."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$2\\sin\\theta\\cos\\theta = 1$",
        "$\\cos 2\\theta = \\cos\\theta$",
        "$\\sin^2\\theta - 2\\sin\\theta - 3 = 0$",
        "$\\cos^2\\theta + \\sin\\theta = 1$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Mixed Applications**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Rewrite $\\sin^4\\theta$ without exponents greater than 1."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Verify: $\\dfrac{\\sin 2\\theta}{1 - \\cos 2\\theta} = \\cot\\theta$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Verify: $\\tan\\dfrac{\\theta}{2} = \\csc\\theta - \\cot\\theta$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If $\\tan\\theta = \\dfrac{3}{4}$ with $\\theta$ in QI, find $\\sin 2\\theta$, \n$\\cos 2\\theta$, and $\\tan 2\\theta$."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Express $\\cos 3\\theta$ in terms of $\\cos\\theta$ only."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Challenge Problems**"
    }
  ]
}